  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6597.22 sitting between the major negative gamma wall at 6590 (-17.2B) and positive gamma peak at 6605 (+20.7B), dealers are positioned in a critical pocket where flows will determine direction. The PIN regime suggests dealers will sell any push toward 6605 and aggressively buy dips toward 6590, creating a tight 15-point range with amplified volatility if 6590 breaks. The gex_surge event combined with massive 1-min and 5-min negative changes indicates rapid positioning shifts that should stabilize around current levels given the strong gamma walls.\n\nKey levels: 6590 downside break triggers dealer buying acceleration, while 6605 upside becomes heavy selling pressure from dealer hedging.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile ping-pong action between 6590-6605 with dealers fighting to keep price in this range.",
